// Bone tumor - Characterization I - I know


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced box in Page 03
And	I'm on Page 04 - Bones of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
And I select ' Bone tumor' from the Finding dropdown
And I select 'I know' radio button
And I select 'Characterization I' tab

Then 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled
And 'Epiphyseal' radio button is enabled
And 'Metaphyseal' radio button is enabled
And 'Margin' radio button is enabled

And 'Sharp' radio button is enabled
And 'Ill-defined' radio button is enabled
And 'Brush-like' radio button is enabled

And 'Inhomogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled

And 'Intact' radio button is enabled
And 'Destruction' radio button is enabled
And 'Thinning ("Scalopping")' radio button is enabled
And 'Penetration' radio button is enabled

And 'Signal T1w' slide bar is enabled
And 'Signal T2w' slide bar is enabled

And 'Strong' radio button is enabled
And 'Weak' radio button is enabled
And 'None' radio button is enabled

And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Entire lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled
And 'Nidus' radio button is enabled

And 'Septations' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fluid level' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Nidus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteoid matrix' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fat signal' checkbox is enabled
And 'Nidus T2w hyperintense' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cap T2w hyperintense' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Benign lesion, not further characterized' from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu is enabled in 'Characterization II' tab 

When I select 'Weak' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Heterogeneous' radio button
Then 'Of the septa' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Calcification' checkbox
Then 'Central' checkbox is enabled
And 'Diffuse' checkbox is enabled
